cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the problem of fake news detection on social media, which involves analyzing user profiles and their sharing behaviors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on information dissemination. 

The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of news articles, which suggests the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely option. 

Additionally, the paper discusses the societal impact of fake news, which aligns with the sub-category cs.SOC (Computers and Society). 

The paper also involves data mining and machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
